+**What**: The accepted spec says the sandboxed process paths should be refactored to lifecycle `try...finally` cleanup, including synchronous failures after `prepareCommand`. Current code still prepares sandbox commands and then invokes `prepared.cleanup?.()` only inside child-process event handlers. If `spawn(...)` throws synchronously after sandbox preparation, the cleanup callback is skipped. The same event-handler-only pattern remains in `spawnAsync`, `GrepToolInvocation.isCommandAvailable`, and `ToolRegistry` discovery/invocation.
